          ],
          "FACILITY": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "VDG"
                ],
                "institute": "2SF HLS"
              },
              "free_text": [
                "2.5MV Van de Graaff accelerator. Proton",
                "currents near 4 micro-A with a beam energy resolution",
                "of  about 600 eV."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Si targets were prepared in the isotope separator. A",
                "set of three targets was made by collecting 1 keV",
                "28Si+,29Si+and 30Si+ions in amounts of 0.6 micro-g/cm2",
                "on 0.4 mm thick tantalum backing.The target thicknesses",
                "were 4.6 micro-g/cm2, which corresponds to the",
                "thickness of 810 keV probed by 1 MeV protons. The",
                "accuracy of the thickness determination is 1%."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "GSPEC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "GELI"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The 110 cm**3 germanium-lithium detector with",
                "an energy resolution of 1.9 keV at Eg=1.33 MeV and 2.9",
                "keV at Eg=2.6 MeV and with an efficiency of 21.8% was",
                "used for gamma detection. The absolute efficiency of",
                "the detector was determined in with the calibrated IAEA",
                "standard sources and using gamma-rays  from reaction",
                "27Al(p,gamma)28Si at Ep=992 keV."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SIBAR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "An annular silicon surface barrier detector with",
                "an active area of 50 mm2 was used for the Ne-C ratios",
                "of the targets using backscattering of alpha-particles.",
                "It was located at a distance of 8 cm from the target",
                "giving a mean scattering angle of 178 degrees. Its",
                "resolution was 14 keV at Ealpha=2.0 MeV."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "GELI"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The 66 cm**3 germanium-lithium detector placed",
                "at a fixed position at a distance of 10 cm from the",
                "target is  used for the angular distribution",
                "measurements at angles 0, 30, 45, 60, 90 degrees."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Corrections were made for:",
                "oxygen contamination - upper limit 1 at.% to Si atoms",
                "eccentricity and absorption -less than 2%."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "In REACTIONs FCT=1/(2Jp+1)(2Jt+1),",
                "where is Jp = spin of incident projectile and",
                "Jt = spin of target nucleus.",
                "In the formula of resonance strength:",
                "          g*Gamma(i)Gamma(j)/Gamma(tot)",
                "instead of usual statistical weight:",
                "  g=(2J+1)/(2Jp+1)(2Jt+1), the authors used g=(2J+1)"
              ]
            }
          ],
